#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Arahantavagga"
msgstr "1. The Perfected Ones"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Aggikasutta"
msgstr "8. With Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn7.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa sappinā pāyaso "
"sannihito hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time ghee and milk-rice had been set out for the brahmin "
"Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper, who thought:"

msgctxt "sn7.8:1.3"
msgid "“aggiṃ juhissāmi, aggihuttaṃ paricarissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I will serve the sacred flame! I will perform the fire sacrifice!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Rājagaha for alms."

msgctxt "sn7.8:2.2"
msgid ""
"Rājagahe sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa "
"nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"Wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Rājagaha, he approached "
"Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s house and stood to one side."

msgctxt "sn7.8:2.3"
msgid "Addasā kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ piṇḍāya ṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper saw him standing for alms"

msgctxt "sn7.8:2.4"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.357"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.1"
msgid "“Tīhi vijjāhi sampanno,"
msgstr "“One who’s accomplished in the three knowledges,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.2"
msgid "jātimā sutavā bahū;"
msgstr "of good lineage and ample learning,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.3"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno,"
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct"

# somaṁ is, sadly, so imaṁ, not a reference to soma.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.4"
msgid "somaṃ bhuñjeyya pāyasan”ti."
msgstr "may enjoy this milk-rice.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.1"
msgid "“Bahumpi palapaṃ jappaṃ,"
msgstr "“Even one who mutters many invocations"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.2"
msgid "na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr "is no brahmin by birth"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.3"
msgid "Antokasambu saṅkiliṭṭho,"
msgstr "if they’re filthy and corrupt within,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.4"
msgid "kuhanāparivārito."
msgstr "with a following gained by fraud."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.167"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.1"
msgid "Pubbenivāsaṃ yo vedī,"
msgstr "But one who knows their past lives,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.2"
msgid "saggāpāyañca passati;"
msgstr "and sees heaven and places of loss,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.3"
msgid "Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto,"
msgstr "and has attained the ending of rebirth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.4"
msgid "abhiññāvosito muni."
msgstr "that sage has perfect insight."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.1"
msgid "Etāhi tīhi vijjāhi,"
msgstr "Because of these three knowledges"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.2"
msgid "tevijjo hoti brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr "a brahmin is a master of the three knowledges."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.3"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno,"
msgstr "Accomplished in knowledge and conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.4"
msgid "somaṃ bhuñjeyya pāyasan”ti."
msgstr "they may enjoy this milk-rice.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.358"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.1"
msgid "“Bhuñjatu bhavaṃ gotamo."
msgstr "“Eat, Master Gotama!"

msgctxt "sn7.8:7.2"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo bhavan”ti."
msgstr "you are truly a brahmin.”"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-chanting-and-enchanting/3376<a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.3"
msgid "“Gāthābhigītaṃ me abhojaneyyaṃ,"
msgstr "“Food enchanted by a spell isn’t fit for me to eat."

# Here sampassata comes close in sense to “empiricist, scientist, rationalist”
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.4"
msgid "Sampassataṃ brāhmaṇa nesa dhammo;"
msgstr "That’s not the way of those who see, brahmin."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.5"
msgid "Gāthābhigītaṃ panudanti buddhā,"
msgstr "The Buddhas reject things enchanted with spells."

# Norman has “doctrine” for Dhamma here, which doesn’t make sense. BB’s “principle” is preferable. I think the sense of the line is “that’s how we live because we’re in a rational universe.” I would compare the locative absolute here with the common ditthevadhamme, i.e. in apparent, empirical existence.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.6"
msgid "Dhamme sati brāhmaṇa vuttiresā."
msgstr "Since nature is real, brahmin, that’s how they live."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.1"
msgid "Aññena ca kevalinaṃ mahesiṃ,"
msgstr "Serve with other food and drink"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.2"
msgid "Khīṇāsavaṃ kukkuccavūpasantaṃ;"
msgstr "the consummate one, the great hermit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.3"
msgid "Annena pānena upaṭṭhahassu,"
msgstr "with defilements ended and remorse stilled."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.4"
msgid "Khettañhi taṃ puññapekkhassa hotī”ti."
msgstr "For he is the field for the seeker of merit.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.8:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.8:10.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! …” …"

msgctxt "sn7.8:10.3"
msgid "aññataro ca panāyasmā aggikabhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr ""
"And Venerable Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper became one of the perfected."
